metadata.title: Beechcraft Bonanza
aws::graph::propositions: Beechcraft Bonanza Model 36 Variants
Model 36 is a revised utility aircraft with similar tail to Model 33.
Model 36 has a 10 inch (25 cm) fuselage stretch.
Model 36 has four cabin windows on each side.
Model 36 has starboard rear double doors.
Model 36 has seats for six passengers.
Model 36 has one 285 hp Continental IO-520-B engine.
Model 36 was produced from 1968 to 1969.
184 Model 36 aircraft were built.
A36 is a variant of Model 36.
A36 has an improved deluxe interior.
A36 has a new fuel system.
A36 has a higher takeoff weight.
A36 was fitted with IO-520-BA or IO-520-BB engines with 285 BHP until 1984.
A36 was fitted with a Continental IO-550-BB 300 BHP engine from 1984.
A36 received a redesigned instrument panel and controls from 1984.
A36 was produced from 1970 to 2005.
2128 A36 aircraft were built.
A36AT is a Model A36 "Airline Trainer" variant.
A36AT has a reduced-diameter propeller.
A36AT has exhaust baffles.
A36AT has reduced RPM to reduce noise for flight schools.

text:
### Model 36 Bonanza

36
(19681969) Revised utility aircraft with similar tail to Model 33 with a 10 in (25 cm) fuselage stretch, four cabin windows each side, starboard rear double doors and seats for six, one 285 hp Continental IO-520-B engine, 184 built.
A36
(19702005) Model 36 with improved deluxe interior, a new fuel system, higher takeoff weight, until 1984 IO-520-BA or IO-520-BB with 285 BHP, from 1984 fitted with a Continental IO-550-BB 300 BHP engine and redesigned instrument panel and controls, 2128 built
A36AT
Model A36 "Airline Trainer" with reduced-diameter propeller, exhaust baffles, and reduced RPM to reduce noise for flight schools.
